A 'Libellula croceipennis' is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae. 
It is commonly known as the golden-winged skimmer due to its distinctive yellow wings. 
This dragonfly species also has a brown body with black markings and a slender appearance. 
It can be found in wetland habitats across North and Central America, particularly in shallow ponds and streams. 
The wings of 'Libellula croceipennis' are delicate with a transparent quality and intricate venation. 
The legs are thin and segmented with small claws at the end. 
The eyes are large and multifaceted with the ability to see in nearly every direction.
